<p>
Upon loading the <a href="/docs/Toolbar">toolbar</a> in your chosen language, the included Javascript file will make the following functions available to your <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a>'s front end Javascript.
</p>

<div class="heading">MinoCloud_setToolbarLoadedCallback(callback)</div>
<p>
<code>callback</code><br />
<code>Type: Function()</code><br />
Called when the <a href="/docs/Toolbar">toolbar</a> successfully loads.
</p>

<div class="heading">MinoCloud_setNotificationCallback(callback)</div>
<p>
<code>callback</code><br />
<code>Type: Function(notification)</code><br />
Called when a new notification for your <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a> arrives. <code>notification</code> is a JSON object.
</p>

<div class="heading">MinoCloud_setConditionalAlertCallback(callback)</div>
<p>
<code>callback</code><br />
<code>Type: Function(notification)</code><br />
Called when a new notification for your <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a> that uses <a href="/docs/Notifications#ConditionalAlerts">conditional alerts</a> arrives. <code>notification</code> is a JSON object. The <code>MinoCloud_respondToConditionalAlert</code> function (below) should be used to send the response.
</p>

<div class="heading">MinoCloud_respondToConditionalAlert(id,shouldAlert)</div>
<p>
<code>id</code><br />
<code>Type: String or Integer</code><br />
The ID of the notification received by the <code>callback</code> set by <code>MinoCloud_setConditionalAlertCallback</code> (above).
<br />
<br />
<code>shouldAlert</code><br />
<code>Type: Boolean</code>
Whether or not the alert should be shown to the user. If any instance of the <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a> chooses not to alert the user then the alert will not be delivered (all instances still receive the notification silently).
</p>

<div class="heading">MinoCloud_setNotificationSelectCallback(callback)</div>
<p>
<code>callback</code><br />
<code>Type: Function(notification)</code><br />
Called when a notification for your <a href="/docs/Apps">app</a> is selected via the <a href="/docs/Toolbar">toolbar</a>.
</p>